<h1>CHAPTER 4: SYSTEM IMPLEMENTATION AND TESTING</h1>

<h2>4.1 Technologies and Tools Used</h2>
<p>The KaviCakes Management System employs a decentralized micro-frontend architecture paired with a centralized backend. Operational files (e.g., payment deposit slips) are stored on local server directories, while static legacy assets utilize Supabase cloud storage. A MySQL relational database guarantees data persistence, enforcing referential integrity between orders, loyalty caps, and dynamic pricing metrics.</p>
<p>By decoupling the React frontend logic from the Express.js API, the system securely processes data externally as JSON payloads, ensuring complex database operations do not block client-side UI rendering threads.</p>

<h2>4.2 Programming Languages and Development Tools</h2>

<h3>4.2.1 Backend — Node.js and Express.js</h3>
<p>The REST API is engineered on Node.js using Express.js due to its asynchronous, non-blocking I/O model, capable of handling concurrent network requests reliably. Prisma ORM securely maps physical database schemas to application models, executing compile-time type validation preventing structural schema drift.</p>
<p>Security is maintained by hashing plaintext passwords via Bcryptjs (10 salt rounds) and enforcing stateless session persistence explicitly via JSON Web Tokens (JWT). Authorization is restricted via role-based middleware prior to query execution. Dynamic transactional processes are handled using Multer for multiform file uploads, Nodemailer connected via specialized SMTP for outbound alerts, and Node-Cron for scheduled background script triggers.</p>

<h3>4.2.2 Admin Web — React and Vite</h3>
<p>Constructed as a Single Page Application using React and bundled by Vite. Admin operations demand high-density data parsing; thus, Ant Design is utilized to render dynamic data grids, scalable forms, and side-loading drawers efficiently. Axios interceptors automatically inject active JWTs into request headers, forcing automatic 401 redirects if tokens naturally expire.</p>

<h3>4.2.3 Customer Web — React and Tailwind CSS</h3>
<p>Tailwind CSS replaces component-heavy libraries to deliver a mobile-first, low-latency UI. Global state propagation utilizes React’s Context API, preventing redundant database calls during Cart accumulation and active Auth session checks.</p>

<h2>4.3 User Interfaces and Interaction Flow</h2>
<p>Client isolation explicitly segregates capabilities between the <code>ADMIN</code> and <code>CUSTOMER</code> roles via strict frontend route guarding and backend database query restrictions.</p>

<h3>4.3.1 Customer Web Capabilities</h3>
<h4>4.3.1.1 Secure Authentication</h4>
<p>Customers execute self-registration restricted by an automated 6-digit email OTP verify loop. React Regex validates passwords in real-time. Unauthorized attempts to fetch admin-level API routes implicitly return 403 Forbidden HTTP codes.</p>

