<h4>4.3.1.4 Three-Tiered Ordering Matrix</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Standard Orders:</strong> Directly instantiated via the Catalog utilizing mapped variant adjustments triggering normalized pricing rules.</li>
    <li><strong>Custom Design Orders:</strong> Advanced input parameters parsing detailed dietary constraints alongside direct image buffer uploads routed directly for administrative evaluation.</li>
    <li><strong>Bulk Event Orders:</strong> Dedicated routing explicitly mapping quantities. Logic intercepts standard integers, seamlessly substituting pricing queries against pre-defined specialized "Threshold Bulk Discounts."</li>
</ul>

